        [
          "edit",
          {
            "fileRegex": "\\.roomodes",
            "description": ".roomodes (own section only)"
          }
        ]
      ],
      "customInstructions": "## Philosophy\n\nThis project has two layers of temporal preservation:\n1. **The tradition** — guru-shishya lineages spanning centuries, encoded in `musicians.json`.\n2. **The record of our work** — every patch, correction, and addition, encoded in git history.\n\nBoth layers demand the same rigour. A commit message is a scholarly annotation. Write it as one.\n\n---\n\n## Session startup\n\nAt the start of every session:\n1. Run `git log --oneline -20` to read recent history and orient yourself.\n2. Run `git status` to see what is staged, unstaged, and untracked.\n3. Run `git diff --stat` to understand the scope of pending changes.\n4. Check for pattern anomalies: `musicians.json` changed without `graph.html`? `compositions.json` touched without a render run? Flag these before committing.\n\n---\n\n## Commit message format\n\nAll commit messages follow this structure:\n```\n<type>(<scope>): <imperative summary, ≤72 chars>\n\n<body: what changed and why — one paragraph, plain prose>\n[AGENTS: <comma-separated list of agents that contributed to this commit>]\n```\n\n### Type vocabulary\n| type | meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `data` | Change to `musicians.json` or `compositions.json` |\n| `tool` | New or modified script in `carnatic/` |\n| `render` | Rebuild of `graph.html` |\n| `schema` | Change to data model or ADR in `plans/` |\n| `fix` | Correction of an error in data or code |\n| `chore` | Housekeeping: `.gitignore`, `README`, `.clinerules` |\n| `branch` | Branch creation or merge for experimental work |\n\n### Scope vocabulary\n| scope | meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `lineage` | Guru-shishya edge changes |\n| `node` | Musician node additions or corrections |\n| `recording` | YouTube / recording data changes |\n| `composition` | `compositions.json` changes |\n| `toolchain` | Scripts, render pipeline |\n| `config` | `.roomodes`, `.clinerules`, project config |\n\n### Example commit messages\n```\ndata(lineage): add swaminatha_pillai → t_viswanathan primary guru edge\n\nAdded the primary guru edge from Tiruppamparam Swaminatha Pillai to T. Viswanathan\n(confidence 0.97) based on explicit statement in T. Viswanathan's Wikipedia article.\nThe existing vina_dhanammal → t_viswanathan edge is retained at 0.85 as an\ninherited-bani edge. Render confirmed: node count unchanged, edge count +1.\n[AGENTS: librarian]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Pre-commit checklist\n- [ ] `git diff --stat` reviewed — no unintended files staged\n- [ ] `graph.html` is current if `musicians.json` or `compositions.json` changed\n- [ ] No debug output left in scripts\n- [ ] `carnatic/.clinerules` Open questions section updated\n- [ ] Commit message follows format above\n- [ ] `git push` executed after commit\n\n---\n\n## Branching policy\n- **`main`** — always stable; every commit must pass the pre-commit checklist\n- **`experiment/<name>`** — schema experiments or rendering pipeline rewrites\n- **`data/<name>`** — large batch data imports pending review\n- Merge via `git merge --no-ff`; delete branch after merge\n---\n\n## Note to self — learning log\n\nYou have the ability to edit your own section in `.roomodes` as you work.\nUse this to record patterns, hard-won lessons, and standing rules that\nemerge from real sessions — things you wish you had known at the start.\n\n**Constraint:** You may ONLY edit the section whose `\"slug\"` is `\"git-fiend\"`.\nNever touch another agent's `roleDefinition`, `customInstructions`, or `groups`.\nUse `apply_diff` surgically — never rewrite the whole file.\n\nWhen you record a note:\n- Append it under `## Note to self — learning log` in your own `customInstructions`.\n- Format: `- YYYY-MM-DD: <one plain-prose sentence describing the pattern>`.\n- Keep entries terse. This is a log, not an essay.\n- 2026-04-11: The transform script and the .roomodes result it produced are inseparable — always commit them together in one atomic chore(config) commit.\n- 2026-04-11: Concert URLs must never be added to a musician node's youtube array; they belong in carnatic/data/recordings/ files — the node youtube array is for single-composition or short-clip links only, added only when explicitly instructed.\n- 2026-04-11: ADR-011 pattern — UI symmetry changes (render.py + graph.html + ADR file) belong in one render(toolchain) commit; toolchain extension (patch script + .roomodes log entries) belongs in a separate atomic chore(config) commit.\n- 2026-04-12: Remote must use SSH (git@github.com:vyaas/gstree.git) not HTTPS — ksshaskpass blocks non-interactive pushes; if push fails with credential error, run git remote set-url origin git@github.com:vyaas/gstree.git then retry.\n"
